preliminary MOG2D data files generated by SALP for the generation of the NTC products. MOG2D allows GDR products to integrate both corrections of the high frequency part of the ocean variability and the low frequency part of the inverse barometer effect. The barotropic corrections are on a regular Cartesian grid 0.25ยบ x 0.25ยบ.

The sun glint risk LUT is expressed as a wave angle characterising the scattering angle around the specular direction.
